CRISP-DM:

BUSINESS UNDERSTANDING:

This is a table about credit card fraud or unpayment.
It is about 28 periods, suppositly months.

DATA UNDERSTANDING:

The data is clear and neat, no missing values in it. It is about 284800 persons and the credit default are on 28 periods.

DATA PREPARATION:

No data preparation just controlling that there is no missing values.

MODELING:

Using sklearn Pandas and matplotlib, a supervised linear regression estimation was done on the model, test sample was about 30%.
r_squared was calculated and the predictions.

A description of the main statistics ratios for the model were given, mean, std, min, max percintile.

A Pearson correlation was also given linking the amount of the fraud to each period.

A graph ploting the amount of the fraud was given at the end. 